WEBVTT

00:07.425 --> 00:09.552
Marco Inaros
has asked us to meet.

00:09.552 --> 00:11.637
- What are we gonya do?
- We will accept.

00:11.637 --> 00:12.596
[Delgado]
Half of Gao's cabinet

00:12.596 --> 00:13.931
was on that plane with her.

00:13.931 --> 00:14.890
The rest were scattered
around the globe.

00:14.890 --> 00:15.933
No one seems to know

00:15.933 --> 00:17.268
who's next in line
of succession.

00:17.268 --> 00:19.353
[Amos] Her mods are blocked.
Her hand is busted.

00:19.353 --> 00:20.896
She is not a threat.

00:20.896 --> 00:22.940
We gotta get out of here.

00:22.940 --> 00:24.900
[Holden] Monica's eye captured
the Zmeya's flight plan.

00:24.900 --> 00:26.986
It's time to take the Roci
out for a hunt.

00:26.986 --> 00:29.822
[suspenseful music]

00:29.822 --> 00:31.073
[gasps]

00:31.073 --> 00:32.324
Did Marco slip

00:32.324 --> 00:34.410
the Augustin Gamarra code
into the Roci?

00:34.410 --> 00:35.870
[sighs]

00:35.870 --> 00:38.998
Jim, do not start
the Roci's drive!

00:38.998 --> 00:40.583
The reactor code's
been sabotaged.

00:40.583 --> 00:41.667
It will blow if you do.

00:41.667 --> 00:42.960
I'm shutting down the reactor.

00:42.960 --> 00:44.879
I'm being held captive
by Marco!

00:45.880 --> 00:47.965
Tell me what happened!
Tell me!

00:47.965 --> 00:49.925
This is Marco Inaros'
Free Navy.

00:49.925 --> 00:52.136
His Belters
on our Martian ships.

00:52.136 --> 00:53.471
Let's get some profiles.

00:53.471 --> 00:54.764
- [computer beeping]
[Alex] Crap, they pinged us.

00:54.764 --> 00:56.515
[engine whooshing]

00:56.515 --> 00:59.518
[tense music]

00:59.518 --> 01:02.062
♪ ♪

01:02.062 --> 01:03.689
We're not gonna make it,
are we?

01:03.689 --> 01:06.192
I got one more thing to try.

01:06.192 --> 01:08.986
♪ ♪

01:08.986 --> 01:12.114
[explosion booms]

01:13.157 --> 01:16.160
[dramatic music]

01:16.160 --> 01:23.167
♪ ♪

01:38.599 --> 01:39.683
Arjun.

01:41.811 --> 01:44.897
Madam Avasarala,
please forgive the intrusion.

01:44.897 --> 01:46.440
I'm David Paster.

01:46.440 --> 01:48.192
We have met.
You're...

01:48.192 --> 01:49.610
Minister of the Interior?

01:49.610 --> 01:51.111
Transportation, actually.

01:51.111 --> 01:52.238
Oh.

01:52.238 --> 01:53.364
Uh...

01:53.364 --> 01:55.825
I'm the new acting
secretary-general.

01:56.784 --> 01:58.619
- Sir.
- No, please, don't get up.

01:58.619 --> 01:59.578
Oh...oh.

02:00.538 --> 02:02.164
Whoa.
[laughs]

02:02.164 --> 02:04.083
Still getting used
to this gravity.

02:06.043 --> 02:08.712
It's my first time off planet,
I'm embarrassed to say.

02:08.712 --> 02:11.423
You'll get the hang of it
soon enough.

02:14.009 --> 02:16.387
I understand
you were in contact

02:16.387 --> 02:19.348
with the secretary-general
when her plane went down.

02:19.348 --> 02:21.100
Yes.

02:21.100 --> 02:23.394
Oh.

02:23.394 --> 02:25.271
I was at the seawall
near the UN

02:25.271 --> 02:27.523
with a sixth grade field trip

02:27.523 --> 02:29.525
when the second rock hit.

02:29.525 --> 02:32.278
As I was being led to safety,

02:32.278 --> 02:35.614
I saw
the Hyongsu Tower collapse.

02:35.614 --> 02:39.285
From the air, I saw half
of midtown underwater.

02:39.285 --> 02:41.203
I've seen the images.

02:42.663 --> 02:43.831
Oh.

02:43.831 --> 02:45.791
Oh, my God.
Yes, of course, your family.

02:45.791 --> 02:48.961
My daughter
and her children are fine.

02:48.961 --> 02:52.172
They're on a shuttle now.
They'll be here soon.

02:52.172 --> 02:53.299
Thank God.

02:53.299 --> 02:55.885
Your husband teaches
at Columbia, doesn't he?

02:55.885 --> 02:58.053
Have you heard from him?

03:00.472 --> 03:04.852
I will pull whatever strings
I can to help locate him.

03:04.852 --> 03:07.229
I appreciate that.

03:07.229 --> 03:09.356
[UNN MP] They're ready for you
in the sit room, sir.

03:09.356 --> 03:11.317
Thank you.

03:13.611 --> 03:17.281
My degree is in drone avionics.

03:17.281 --> 03:21.368
I spent my career designing
package delivery systems.

03:21.368 --> 03:23.120
The only reason I got
into Parliament is because

03:23.120 --> 03:25.539
I thought the person running
the local transit authority

03:25.539 --> 03:29.043
was an idiot and I thought
I could do a much better job,

03:29.043 --> 03:30.127
and I won his seat.

03:30.127 --> 03:32.212
[chuckles]

03:32.212 --> 03:35.758
We were only able
to beat back the attack

03:35.758 --> 03:37.259
because of you.

03:38.427 --> 03:41.138
I'd like you to join
my provisional cabinet.

03:42.598 --> 03:44.016
Please.

03:45.809 --> 03:47.311
Of course.

03:48.145 --> 03:49.480
Thank you, madam.

03:49.480 --> 03:54.109
♪ ♪

03:54.109 --> 03:57.404
I'll be with you in a moment,
Secretary-General.

03:57.404 --> 04:04.411
♪ ♪

04:20.719 --> 04:22.221
Damn it.

04:35.442 --> 04:37.069
[sighs]

04:37.069 --> 04:43.283
♪ ♪

04:51.208 --> 04:54.253
[wind whooshing]

05:28.746 --> 05:31.749
[drone whirring]

05:36.837 --> 05:38.464
[announcer] Please present
your identification

05:38.464 --> 05:40.215
upon arrival.

05:40.215 --> 05:41.592
If you do not have any ID,

05:41.592 --> 05:44.595
proceed to the DNA tent
at the north entrance.

05:44.595 --> 05:47.139
[indistinct chatter]

05:48.432 --> 05:51.143
If you are injured or in need
of medical attention,

05:51.143 --> 05:53.312
please proceed directly
to the triage area.

05:53.312 --> 05:55.773
[coughing]

05:55.773 --> 05:57.316
[spits]

05:59.401 --> 06:01.945
You feeling better?

06:01.945 --> 06:03.489
No.

06:03.489 --> 06:06.033
There might be something
at the aid station.

06:07.076 --> 06:08.535
There's police there.

06:09.870 --> 06:11.872
I don't want to go back
to prison.

06:11.872 --> 06:13.082
Well, there's no prison
to go back to.

06:13.082 --> 06:14.083
They'll probably
just shoot you.

06:14.083 --> 06:16.251
I don't want that either.

06:16.251 --> 06:17.503
In that case,

06:17.503 --> 06:20.547
I'm thinking our best bet
is Baltimore.

06:20.547 --> 06:22.257
I know some people there,

06:22.257 --> 06:24.510
the kind you want to be around
in times like this.

06:26.512 --> 06:29.473
We could cut through
the Conservancy Zone.

06:29.473 --> 06:31.350
We'll be a lot less likely
to bump into people

06:31.350 --> 06:33.060
we don't want to bump into.

06:35.354 --> 06:37.689
It's a long way.

06:37.689 --> 06:38.982
You up for that?

06:40.317 --> 06:41.360
I'll make it.

06:42.778 --> 06:44.404
All right.

06:44.404 --> 06:51.411
♪ ♪

07:04.716 --> 07:06.593
[engine revving]

07:06.593 --> 07:08.053
[Holden] How's the reactor?

07:08.053 --> 07:12.099
Holding steady at 10%.
All diagnostic in normal range.

07:12.099 --> 07:15.102
Okay fo reboot da system
on lower deck, ke?

07:15.102 --> 07:17.479
- Yeah, do it.
- Aye, aye, Captain.

07:23.735 --> 07:27.823
[indistinct chatter]

07:27.823 --> 07:30.909
So where should I stow this?

07:30.909 --> 07:32.411
Oh, no fucking way.

07:32.411 --> 07:34.997
Monica,
this is a military operation.

07:34.997 --> 07:38.375
The only reason you have a shot
at catching the Zmeya

07:38.375 --> 07:39.960
is because of me,
and I have a story to write.

07:39.960 --> 07:41.420
- Too bad.
- So if you want me

07:41.420 --> 07:43.755
off this ship,
you're gonna have to drag me.

07:43.755 --> 07:45.007
You got it.

07:45.007 --> 07:47.009
No, look, I've already
been kidnapped once.

07:47.009 --> 07:49.052
For all we know, there could be
more Inaros goons

07:49.052 --> 07:50.971
running around on Tycho.

07:50.971 --> 07:53.140
I'd rather
take my chances here.

07:56.310 --> 07:57.811
You know,
when we find these pricks,

07:57.811 --> 08:00.063
the ride's gonna get
a little rough.

08:00.063 --> 08:01.899
You ever been
in high-G maneuvers before?

08:01.899 --> 08:04.443
Mm-hmm.
On this ship...

08:04.443 --> 08:06.028
when we were the first people

08:06.028 --> 08:07.738
to go through the Ring
and survive.

08:10.032 --> 08:13.035
[suspenseful music]

08:13.035 --> 08:20.042
♪ ♪

08:21.543 --> 08:24.546
[engine whooshing]

08:28.091 --> 08:29.509
Make sure
your vac suit's ready.

08:29.509 --> 08:30.594
You'll be needing it soon.

08:30.594 --> 08:31.929
Will do.

08:41.188 --> 08:43.690
Monica Stuart
is authorized for ship systems,

08:43.690 --> 08:45.859
guest access privileges only.

08:51.573 --> 08:54.576
[dramatic music]

08:54.576 --> 09:01.583
♪ ♪

09:06.546 --> 09:09.549
[pensive instrumental music]

09:09.549 --> 09:16.515
♪ ♪

09:24.815 --> 09:27.818
[woman singing in Norwegian]

09:47.462 --> 09:54.469
♪ ♪

10:31.965 --> 10:34.968
[ominous music]

10:34.968 --> 10:41.975
♪ ♪

10:43.643 --> 10:47.939
[mechanical whirring]

10:47.939 --> 10:54.946
♪ ♪

11:22.682 --> 11:26.353
[gunfire]

11:27.687 --> 11:29.773
[tense music]

11:29.773 --> 11:31.566
[Bobbie] Alex, now!
- [Alex grunts]

11:31.566 --> 11:35.195
♪ ♪

11:35.195 --> 11:36.488
[grunts]

11:36.488 --> 11:37.656
[gunfire]

11:37.656 --> 11:44.663
♪ ♪

11:51.169 --> 11:52.170
[grunts]

11:54.673 --> 11:56.758
Alex, he's trying to push off.
Hurry.

11:56.758 --> 11:57.759
[grunts]

12:00.220 --> 12:01.304
[panting]

12:01.304 --> 12:03.849
[grunting]

12:07.853 --> 12:11.773
Alex, I can't hold on
for much longer.

12:11.773 --> 12:12.774
Grenade is set.

12:14.192 --> 12:16.153
[computer beeping]

12:17.529 --> 12:18.822
[yells]

12:21.867 --> 12:24.578
Alex, I couldn't hold them!
Are you back?

12:24.578 --> 12:26.788
Alex?
You gotta get back.

12:26.788 --> 12:27.831
Now!

12:27.831 --> 12:30.417
I'm coming!

12:30.417 --> 12:33.420
[dramatic music]

12:33.420 --> 12:40.427
♪ ♪

12:43.555 --> 12:45.390
[grunts]

12:47.267 --> 12:49.102
Get your ass inside now.

12:49.102 --> 12:56.109
♪ ♪

13:00.906 --> 13:02.782
Emergency start-up, go!

13:02.782 --> 13:04.034
[engine whooshing]

13:04.034 --> 13:10.999
♪ ♪

13:13.543 --> 13:16.755
We did it!
Suck on that, motherfuckers!

13:16.755 --> 13:19.341
[both cheering]

13:19.341 --> 13:21.510
[laughs]

13:21.510 --> 13:24.513
[engines whooshing]

13:26.306 --> 13:28.141
And so instead
of a grand symbol

13:28.141 --> 13:31.478
of Inner-Belter unity destroyed
along with half of Tycho,

13:31.478 --> 13:33.772
the Rocinante is underway...

13:33.772 --> 13:35.815
in pursuit of the Zmeya.

13:35.815 --> 13:37.442
I'm sorry.
It's my fault.

13:37.442 --> 13:39.277
I should have never
let Naomi near a comm.

13:39.277 --> 13:41.029
She never should have been here
in the first place.

13:41.029 --> 13:42.739
I'm sorry I brought her.

13:47.494 --> 13:48.995
Space her.

13:52.499 --> 13:53.750
What?

13:53.750 --> 13:55.544
You heard me.

13:55.544 --> 13:58.255
Stop apologizing,
and correct your error

13:58.255 --> 14:00.090
and put her outside.

14:00.090 --> 14:01.633
Marco...

14:01.633 --> 14:04.719
We treated her with respect,

14:04.719 --> 14:06.513
and she betrayed us,

14:06.513 --> 14:08.723
gave aid to our enemies,
tried to take my life!

14:08.723 --> 14:10.725
- I know, but...
- What?

14:10.725 --> 14:13.603
It's Naomi.

14:13.603 --> 14:16.856
- You will show her mercy?
- I'll keep her in her cell.

14:16.856 --> 14:18.233
After what
she nearly did to me...

14:18.233 --> 14:19.609
You'll never have
to see her again, I swear.

14:19.609 --> 14:20.986
[Marco]
You will do what I tell you to.

14:20.986 --> 14:22.779
Do it yourself!

14:27.492 --> 14:30.537
If it has to be done,
you can do it.

14:30.537 --> 14:33.915
I'm not gonna let Filip
be part of this,

14:33.915 --> 14:36.251
unless you think
you can make me, hmm?

14:36.251 --> 14:39.337
Maybe I finally
got old enough, huh?

14:44.259 --> 14:48.930
Filip, if the choice
was yours to make...

14:49.973 --> 14:51.558
...what would it be?

14:53.560 --> 14:55.228
Oh, don't look at him.

14:56.021 --> 14:58.023
- I asked you.
- Spare her life.

14:58.023 --> 15:00.942
[tense music]

15:00.942 --> 15:02.485
Please.

15:02.485 --> 15:05.530
♪ ♪

15:05.530 --> 15:08.199
My son...

15:08.199 --> 15:11.494
has a kind heart.

15:11.494 --> 15:18.001
♪ ♪

15:22.672 --> 15:24.633
I have more important
things to do.

15:24.633 --> 15:31.431
♪ ♪

15:33.391 --> 15:35.518
Would you really have
spaced her?

15:39.230 --> 15:40.607
What do you think?

15:40.607 --> 15:44.611
I think that if you
do want it done...

15:44.611 --> 15:46.738
next time, ask me.

15:49.115 --> 15:52.118
[dramatic music]

15:52.118 --> 15:53.953
♪ ♪

15:53.953 --> 15:55.664
I'm sorry.

15:55.664 --> 15:57.666
I know.
You've said.

16:02.754 --> 16:04.964
So am I.

16:04.964 --> 16:08.301
I've never seen the two of you
like that before.

16:08.301 --> 16:10.428
I thought you were
going to come to blows.

16:12.347 --> 16:14.265
Wouldn't be the first time.

16:14.265 --> 16:21.272
♪ ♪

16:27.153 --> 16:30.281
You deserve to die
for what you did.

16:30.281 --> 16:31.574
[laughs]

16:31.574 --> 16:33.576
You think that's funny?

16:33.576 --> 16:34.994
No...

16:34.994 --> 16:37.580
but I can tell
my people are all right.

16:37.580 --> 16:39.833
Your people.

16:39.833 --> 16:42.627
You don't even think of
our family as your own anymore.

16:45.130 --> 16:46.756
I guess I don't.

16:48.883 --> 16:51.678
And I'm more sorry about that
than you'll ever know.

16:54.139 --> 16:56.433
You would never have
been able to hurt him.

16:57.475 --> 16:58.852
You would have been killed.

16:58.852 --> 17:00.311
I knew that.

17:02.564 --> 17:05.567
It would've been
the last thing I ever did.

17:05.567 --> 17:08.153
But it would've been worth it.

17:10.613 --> 17:13.283
It's the only thing left
I can do to help you...

17:13.283 --> 17:15.869
He's a visionary...

17:15.869 --> 17:19.789
doing what no other Belter
has ever dreamed.

17:19.789 --> 17:21.207
He took the Belt
back from the Inners...

17:21.207 --> 17:23.543
He's made you a murderer.

17:25.128 --> 17:28.423
You ended millions

17:28.423 --> 17:30.550
of ordinary lives.

17:30.550 --> 17:32.886
You haven't felt
the price of it yet,

17:32.886 --> 17:36.139
but someday, you will.

17:36.139 --> 17:39.350
And you will realize
what he's done to you.

17:39.350 --> 17:41.895
He made me a fighter.

17:41.895 --> 17:43.980
- He loves me.
- He loves himself.

17:43.980 --> 17:45.315
Oh, you don't know
anything about him.

17:45.315 --> 17:48.902
I know he wouldn't
die for you...

17:48.902 --> 17:51.154
but he would
let you die for him.

17:51.154 --> 17:58.161
♪ ♪

18:38.827 --> 18:40.829
[Clarissa] It's so pretty.

18:42.580 --> 18:44.707
[Amos] I didn't know there were
so many trees in the world.

18:46.167 --> 18:47.961
[Clarissa] This is one of
the first reforestation trials

18:47.961 --> 18:49.838
in North America.

18:49.838 --> 18:51.923
It's been around
almost 150 years.

18:54.092 --> 18:55.385
[Amos] Yeah?

18:55.385 --> 18:58.054
[Clarissa] You never came up
on a field trip?

18:58.054 --> 18:59.097
[Amos] No.

19:00.431 --> 19:03.434
[Clarissa] I thought everyone
had to come plant a tree

19:03.434 --> 19:06.604
for a week and appreciate
the carbon cycle.

19:06.604 --> 19:07.897
[Amos] Not me.

19:09.983 --> 19:13.278
[Clarissa] This was one
of my grandfather's charities.

19:13.278 --> 19:16.322
My family helped fund it.
Dad kept it up after he died.

19:18.616 --> 19:21.035
[Amos] Something in it for him?

19:21.035 --> 19:22.245
[Clarissa] No.

19:24.789 --> 19:28.793
I think...
Dad just liked trees.

19:31.337 --> 19:34.340
[groaning]

19:35.842 --> 19:36.968
You okay?

19:36.968 --> 19:40.263
[breathing heavily]

19:40.263 --> 19:42.557
I'm just burning
through the last

19:42.557 --> 19:44.100
of the implant-blocking agents,

19:44.100 --> 19:47.020
and it's making
my muscles cramp.

19:47.020 --> 19:49.272
That's all it is.

19:49.272 --> 19:50.899
You sure?

19:52.817 --> 19:54.277
No.

19:58.323 --> 20:05.330
♪ ♪

20:16.925 --> 20:18.384
[Clarissa] Is he alive?

20:20.011 --> 20:21.137
No.

20:22.347 --> 20:25.224
Sit down.
I'll take care of this.

20:38.196 --> 20:39.614
So he's dead?

20:39.614 --> 20:40.865
You said he was.

20:41.783 --> 20:43.451
No, your dad.

20:43.451 --> 20:46.537
You said that he liked trees,
not that he likes trees.

20:46.537 --> 20:48.873
I hadn't heard that he died.

20:48.873 --> 20:52.251
But I don't watch
the news feeds much.

20:52.251 --> 20:55.171
I don't think he's dead...

20:55.171 --> 20:58.633
but after I went into prison,
I didn't hear from him...

20:58.633 --> 21:00.551
at all.

21:01.594 --> 21:03.846
Schrodinger's parent.

21:04.597 --> 21:05.515
Who?

21:08.601 --> 21:13.147
A parent you never hear from
exists in a quantum state,

21:13.147 --> 21:16.067
both dead and alive,
until you check up on them

21:16.067 --> 21:17.694
and the act of observing

21:17.694 --> 21:19.612
makes one
of the two states true.

21:20.571 --> 21:22.865
I might have a dad somewhere
I never met.

21:22.865 --> 21:24.701
Do you want to?

21:26.327 --> 21:27.996
Nope.

21:27.996 --> 21:29.998
Then does he
actually exist at all?

21:36.462 --> 21:37.922
- You want some?
- Nah.

21:37.922 --> 21:39.382
You go ahead.

21:51.227 --> 21:52.895
What about your mother?

21:52.895 --> 21:55.273
She died young.

21:55.273 --> 21:56.774
What about genetic markers?

21:58.901 --> 22:00.319
I didn't check.

22:02.113 --> 22:04.157
I did have someone...

22:04.157 --> 22:06.075
who tried to take care of me.

22:07.535 --> 22:09.495
She died not too long ago.

22:11.873 --> 22:14.542
She showed up...

22:14.542 --> 22:16.586
so she's a parent
that actually existed.

22:18.963 --> 22:20.048
I don't mean to make light.

22:20.048 --> 22:22.341
I'm sure
she's a really good person.

22:22.341 --> 22:25.011
She lived like she was.

22:25.011 --> 22:26.429
What does that mean?

22:28.723 --> 22:31.434
There are ways that you
can live a good life...

22:31.434 --> 22:33.269
without being a good person.

22:36.189 --> 22:38.191
I like that.

22:41.235 --> 22:42.862
No.

22:51.913 --> 22:53.790
Do you need
a little bit longer?

22:56.042 --> 22:57.085
I can keep going.

22:57.085 --> 23:04.092
♪ ♪

23:04.092 --> 23:07.261
It's funny
if you think about it.

23:07.261 --> 23:09.222
What?

23:09.222 --> 23:10.515
The moon.

23:12.809 --> 23:14.811
For almost all
of human history,

23:14.811 --> 23:16.687
it was impossible
to go there,

23:16.687 --> 23:20.608
a symbol of something you
could only do in your dreams.

23:20.608 --> 23:22.568
And then for a while,
it was hard but possible.

23:22.568 --> 23:24.362
And then it was trivial.

23:24.362 --> 23:27.115
And now here we are,
and it's impossible again.

23:29.617 --> 23:30.868
[Amos] Pretty sure
that's the sun,

23:30.868 --> 23:33.204
but I get your point.

23:35.790 --> 23:37.500
I need to rest.

23:39.252 --> 23:40.128
Look.

23:51.472 --> 23:54.016
I don't have anything
worth taking.

23:54.016 --> 23:55.226
Come take a look
if you want.

23:55.226 --> 23:57.436
Just leave me be.

23:57.436 --> 23:58.896
[Clarissa] We're not robbers.

23:58.896 --> 24:00.231
[man]
Then what are you?

24:00.231 --> 24:01.899
Just people on the road.

24:02.859 --> 24:04.527
Where you headed?

24:04.527 --> 24:06.404
North.

24:06.404 --> 24:08.281
UN's setting up a relief camp.

24:11.993 --> 24:13.119
Take a seat if you want.

24:26.382 --> 24:28.176
Nice coat.

24:28.176 --> 24:29.385
[Clarissa] Thanks.

24:30.553 --> 24:32.388
We're headed to Baltimore.

24:32.388 --> 24:34.265
Have you heard anything?

24:34.265 --> 24:36.934
Only that you'd be
better off coming with me.

24:36.934 --> 24:38.436
It's flooding on the coast,

24:38.436 --> 24:41.063
all the shit
hitting the fan.

24:41.063 --> 24:43.024
The cities are a sneeze
and a slap away

24:43.024 --> 24:45.318
from everyone killing
each other over a can of ham.

24:45.318 --> 24:47.862
[Clarissa coughing]

24:47.862 --> 24:49.947
You feeling all right, miss?

24:49.947 --> 24:51.324
You look a little pale.

24:52.992 --> 24:54.827
I, um, broke my hand.

24:56.996 --> 24:58.414
I do have a little something
we could drink.

25:00.875 --> 25:03.502
It's not much, but...
take the edge off the cold.

25:03.502 --> 25:05.338
No, thank you.

25:05.338 --> 25:06.881
We should get going.

25:08.049 --> 25:10.092
I'd recommend
you head due south a ways

25:10.092 --> 25:12.386
before you cut east.

25:12.386 --> 25:14.472
There's a guy that's
fenced off a couple acres,

25:14.472 --> 25:17.850
and he's offering to shoot
anyone who comes too close.

25:17.850 --> 25:19.518
Why?

25:19.518 --> 25:22.104
One of these
"end of times" fellas.

25:22.104 --> 25:24.065
Probably can't believe
how lucky he is

25:24.065 --> 25:25.775
all this happened.

25:27.026 --> 25:29.779
Thank you.
We'll keep an eye out.

25:29.779 --> 25:32.782
[tense music]

25:32.782 --> 25:39.789
♪ ♪

25:51.175 --> 25:53.803
Could've stood that drink...

25:53.803 --> 25:56.597
maybe a few more hours
by that fire.

25:56.597 --> 25:58.933
I feel like I haven't
been warm in years.

26:02.144 --> 26:04.105
What's going on?

26:05.398 --> 26:07.483
Making sure
he's not following us.

26:07.483 --> 26:09.944
- He was harmless.
[Amos] Maybe.

26:09.944 --> 26:14.073
The thing about civilization
is, it keeps you civil.

26:14.073 --> 26:16.367
Get rid of one,
you can't count on the other.

26:18.661 --> 26:20.538
It's like
you've done this before.

26:20.538 --> 26:23.249
I grew up like this.

26:23.249 --> 26:25.459
Everyone else
is just playing catch-up.

26:25.459 --> 26:27.545
People are tribal.

26:27.545 --> 26:29.297
The more settled things are,

26:29.297 --> 26:31.799
the bigger the tribes can be.

26:31.799 --> 26:34.677
The churn comes,
and the tribes get small again.

26:35.886 --> 26:38.055
Right now,
you and I are a tribe of two.

26:38.973 --> 26:40.641
That's better than one.

26:45.021 --> 26:47.023
I don't think he's coming.

26:48.149 --> 26:50.735
Yeah.
Good.

26:53.195 --> 26:55.781
We'll go this way.

26:55.781 --> 26:57.908
Towards the crazy asshole
who's shooting people?

26:57.908 --> 26:59.785
Yep.

27:00.870 --> 27:04.040
[dramatic music]

27:04.040 --> 27:11.047
♪ ♪

27:20.973 --> 27:23.142
[Oksana]
Are you worried about Camina?

27:24.185 --> 27:25.436
Are you?

27:26.896 --> 27:28.647
I asked you first.

27:28.647 --> 27:33.152
♪ ♪

27:33.152 --> 27:36.155
[Josep]
I'm worried about us...

27:36.155 --> 27:37.615
all of us,

27:37.615 --> 27:39.200
especially Camina.

27:42.661 --> 27:44.205
So your answer is yes.

27:46.665 --> 27:48.376
[Josep] Her loss...

27:48.376 --> 27:50.044
her losses...

27:50.044 --> 27:51.962
are still fresh.

27:53.005 --> 27:54.632
I worry about that.

27:56.467 --> 27:57.968
Me too.

28:00.179 --> 28:02.848
We cannot let her
do anything rash.

28:02.848 --> 28:05.226
I know.
She won't.

28:06.560 --> 28:07.603
If she does...

28:07.603 --> 28:11.023
We will make sure
she does not.

28:12.274 --> 28:14.985
- [computer beeping]
- Contact, incoming.

28:14.985 --> 28:17.822
Multiple contacts,
separate headings.

28:17.822 --> 28:18.906
They're jamming our comms.

28:18.906 --> 28:21.909
[suspenseful music]

28:21.909 --> 28:24.495
♪ ♪

28:24.495 --> 28:26.872
One MCRN light cruiser.

28:26.872 --> 28:28.332
Two heavy frigate.

28:28.332 --> 28:30.835
[Michio] We've been ambushed.
[Serge] More incoming.

28:30.835 --> 28:34.463
Two...no, three Belter ships
trailing also.

28:35.631 --> 28:38.634
[Bertold] Captain, connection
request on tight-beam.

28:38.634 --> 28:40.052
To me.

28:43.973 --> 28:46.142
The Free Navy welcomes us.

28:47.726 --> 28:49.812
We are being asked to dock.

28:49.812 --> 28:53.566
MCRN warships...
how could Marco have these?

28:55.651 --> 28:57.236
That's a good question.

28:57.236 --> 28:59.321
But so much
for shooting our way out.

28:59.321 --> 29:01.824
♪ ♪

29:01.824 --> 29:04.827
[engines whooshing]

29:04.827 --> 29:11.834
♪ ♪

29:13.127 --> 29:16.172
Welcome to the Pella.

29:16.172 --> 29:18.549
Give me your weapon.

29:18.549 --> 29:20.718
Your temper precedes you.

29:21.635 --> 29:23.220
If I refuse?

29:23.220 --> 29:27.016
Then turn around and go back
to your little ships...

29:27.016 --> 29:28.893
as our enemy.

29:28.893 --> 29:35.900
♪ ♪

29:48.621 --> 29:50.414
[Drummer]
That one is with Black Sky.

29:50.414 --> 29:52.208
[Oksana]
I think she is Golden Bough.

29:52.208 --> 29:53.501
Tributes.

29:53.501 --> 29:56.045
They come here in exchange
for Inaros on their ships.

29:56.045 --> 29:59.006
Marco is consolidating support
amongst the factions.

29:59.006 --> 30:03.552
If Marco has Black Sky
and Golden Bough with him,

30:03.552 --> 30:06.388
half the OPA
will rally to his banner.

30:07.848 --> 30:14.855
♪ ♪

30:21.445 --> 30:24.031
Drummer...

30:24.031 --> 30:25.908
and associates.

30:25.908 --> 30:28.494
Thank you for coming.

30:28.494 --> 30:30.663
No throne?

30:30.663 --> 30:32.873
- This is a war room.
- For a war you started.

30:32.873 --> 30:34.833
- For a war I won.
- Is it over?

30:34.833 --> 30:37.545
I must have missed the Inners'
offer of surrender.

30:42.508 --> 30:45.302
I knew there was
a reason I liked you.

30:45.302 --> 30:47.137
Do you know who I liked?

30:47.137 --> 30:48.639
That's easy to guess.

30:48.639 --> 30:51.725
You came here in his ship.

30:51.725 --> 30:54.853
You know the song he sang
when you spaced him,

30:54.853 --> 30:56.897
it wasn't fear.

30:56.897 --> 30:59.400
He used to sing it
to his daughter

30:59.400 --> 31:02.570
and to keep his mind steady
in trying times.

31:02.570 --> 31:04.655
A sentimental man.

31:04.655 --> 31:06.865
You killed him,
and you killed Fred.

31:06.865 --> 31:09.994
They fought and lost and died

31:09.994 --> 31:12.454
because they betrayed
all Belters

31:12.454 --> 31:14.248
to do the Inners' bidding...

31:16.834 --> 31:18.752
...which you would not.

31:18.752 --> 31:21.630
I'm beginning
to regret my decision.

31:21.630 --> 31:25.426
Marco, we came to talk
about the future, not the past.

31:25.426 --> 31:27.386
Yes. What about food?

31:27.386 --> 31:29.471
Earth is the only source
for live soil

31:29.471 --> 31:31.599
and complex biologicals.

31:31.599 --> 31:34.226
Beltalowda still need to eat.

31:34.226 --> 31:38.522
Those...are good questions

31:38.522 --> 31:41.609
which deserve serious answers.

31:43.319 --> 31:48.032
Earth has always used
agriculture to control us.

31:50.284 --> 31:53.662
Here are some facts and figures
from Nico Sanjrani.

31:53.662 --> 31:55.539
You might have heard of him
from a little project

31:55.539 --> 31:58.709
he was involved in,
the Ganymede AgDomes.

32:00.127 --> 32:02.963
There will be thin years
at first,

32:02.963 --> 32:04.340
but within a decade,

32:04.340 --> 32:05.674
the Belt will have

32:05.674 --> 32:08.469
the agricultural
production levels of Earth...

32:10.220 --> 32:12.097
...and surpass it.

32:16.977 --> 32:19.438
Free of colonial control,

32:19.438 --> 32:22.858
we will have no limit.

32:22.858 --> 32:26.487
I invite you
to join the Free Navy.

32:26.487 --> 32:30.991
Add your strength,
your reputation

32:30.991 --> 32:32.326
to ours.

32:33.827 --> 32:37.456
- Or else?
- Or leave.

32:37.456 --> 32:39.708
And go in peace.

32:39.708 --> 32:42.461
But do not expect me
to protect you.

32:44.254 --> 32:47.257
The only reason
we need protection

32:47.257 --> 32:49.843
is because of you.

32:49.843 --> 32:52.638
You have committed
the entire Belt

32:52.638 --> 32:56.183
to war with the Inners
and made peace impossible.

32:56.183 --> 33:00.312
[Marco] I committed us
to a future of our own

33:00.312 --> 33:02.481
on our own terms.

33:02.481 --> 33:05.651
We were already at war.

33:07.986 --> 33:09.530
You just couldn't see it

33:09.530 --> 33:12.783
because they were
killing us slow.

33:18.706 --> 33:21.750
Talk amongst yourselves.

33:21.750 --> 33:23.585
Make a decision...

33:23.585 --> 33:26.630
and do it quickly.

33:26.630 --> 33:28.882
We won't be staying here long.

33:28.882 --> 33:31.885
[dramatic music]

33:31.885 --> 33:38.892
♪ ♪

34:09.590 --> 34:10.799
Amos.

34:19.391 --> 34:20.976
Fresh blood.

34:23.187 --> 34:25.439
So they tried
to go over the fence.

34:27.900 --> 34:30.569
You sure this is a good idea?

34:30.569 --> 34:33.197
We won't go over the fence.

34:39.995 --> 34:42.998
[suspenseful music]

34:42.998 --> 34:49.171
♪ ♪

34:49.171 --> 34:52.174
[groaning]

34:55.385 --> 34:58.096
It's okay. It's okay.
It'll pass.

35:05.813 --> 35:07.314
Stay hidden.

35:12.945 --> 35:19.618
♪ ♪

35:21.787 --> 35:25.165
And if anything goes bad, run.

35:25.165 --> 35:32.172
♪ ♪

35:40.722 --> 35:42.307
[Amos] Hello?

35:45.686 --> 35:47.020
Anyone there?

36:00.075 --> 36:02.536
I'm not disrespecting
your property, sir.

36:03.704 --> 36:05.372
Just want to talk trade.

36:06.039 --> 36:07.541
Don't shoot me.

36:11.795 --> 36:13.589
You stepped on my land.

36:13.589 --> 36:17.384
I did, but I announced myself.

36:17.384 --> 36:18.969
I heard you had rifles.

36:18.969 --> 36:22.431
I do, and my son does too.

36:26.476 --> 36:28.061
What's it to you?

36:28.061 --> 36:30.647
I got a water recycler.

36:30.647 --> 36:33.150
I just need something to hunt
food on my way up north.

36:33.150 --> 36:34.943
Where is the recycler?

36:36.612 --> 36:39.406
Just off the trail,
half a click south.

36:40.115 --> 36:41.825
Stop where you are,

36:41.825 --> 36:44.578
or you won't need to worry
about hunting.

36:45.454 --> 36:46.955
Throw down your weapons.

36:46.955 --> 36:49.791
I don't have any weapons.
That's why I'm here.

36:49.791 --> 36:50.959
Strip, then.

36:50.959 --> 36:53.086
What?

36:53.086 --> 36:54.379
You say you don't have
any weapons.

36:54.379 --> 36:56.381
Stand where you are
and strip down.

36:57.507 --> 36:59.801
Once I know you're clean,
we'll talk.

37:03.430 --> 37:10.437
♪ ♪

37:30.707 --> 37:33.710
Now, unless you think
I got a pistol up my ass,

37:33.710 --> 37:36.129
we both can agree I'm unarmed.

37:36.129 --> 37:38.966
Recycler's worth more
than an extra rifle.

37:39.967 --> 37:43.095
Yeah, but I can go get
that cycler myself.

37:44.096 --> 37:45.847
Don't need you.

37:46.807 --> 37:49.017
[high-pitched ringing]

37:51.478 --> 37:54.731
- [Clarissa shrieking]
- [man grunting]

37:57.776 --> 38:00.320
[high-pitched ringing]

38:00.320 --> 38:01.446
[gunshot]

38:03.907 --> 38:05.742
[Clarissa inhales sharply]

38:06.535 --> 38:09.162
[groans]

38:09.162 --> 38:12.040
[panting]

38:14.001 --> 38:17.004
[soft dramatic music]

38:17.004 --> 38:24.011
♪ ♪

38:38.900 --> 38:41.403
[moaning]

38:43.864 --> 38:45.699
[retches]

38:47.868 --> 38:49.703
[coughs]

39:01.506 --> 39:03.467
[sighs]

39:07.721 --> 39:14.728
♪ ♪

39:35.373 --> 39:38.210
[whispering]
Monsters...

39:38.210 --> 39:40.045
not afraid.

39:42.130 --> 39:43.840
Monsters...

39:43.840 --> 39:47.260
not afraid.

39:47.260 --> 39:54.267
♪ ♪

39:59.147 --> 40:01.274
If he said we can go,
I say we go.

40:01.274 --> 40:03.068
Go where?

40:03.068 --> 40:04.653
You think the Earthers
are going to care

40:04.653 --> 40:06.863
whose side we say we're on?

40:06.863 --> 40:08.657
They will kill
every Belter they find.

40:08.657 --> 40:09.908
- They always have.
[Josep] If we join Marco,

40:09.908 --> 40:11.451
at least we'll have protection.

40:11.451 --> 40:13.578
- He's a mass murderer.
- And we cannot trust him.

40:13.578 --> 40:15.080
When someone is coming
to kill me,

40:15.080 --> 40:17.124
the biggest mass murderer
in history

40:17.124 --> 40:18.708
watching my back
sounds pretty good.

40:18.708 --> 40:20.794
If we join him,
we are no better than he is.

40:20.794 --> 40:22.379
We have to join.

40:23.964 --> 40:25.549
There's no choice.

40:26.675 --> 40:29.386
Marco says it's a choice...

40:29.386 --> 40:31.680
and we are all acting
like that's true.

40:34.057 --> 40:35.225
But it's not.

40:36.601 --> 40:41.231
Earth will go to war
with the Belt,

40:41.231 --> 40:43.608
and our only chance
we have to survive

40:43.608 --> 40:45.610
is if we stand together.

40:45.610 --> 40:47.654
This is Marco's war,

40:47.654 --> 40:49.072
not mine, not ours.

40:49.072 --> 40:50.657
It doesn't matter.

40:50.657 --> 40:52.993
He's gonna accomplish
what a century of leaders

40:52.993 --> 40:56.496
have promised
and failed to do...

40:56.496 --> 40:59.583
what Anderson Dawes and...

40:59.583 --> 41:01.293
and Fred Johnson could not.

41:03.253 --> 41:06.381
He's gonna unite
a hundred separate factions

41:06.381 --> 41:08.758
into one nation.

41:11.011 --> 41:13.638
And the only choice
left for us...

41:14.973 --> 41:16.516
...is to join him...

41:18.602 --> 41:19.895
or die.

41:19.895 --> 41:22.898
[dramatic music]

41:22.898 --> 41:29.779
♪ ♪

41:39.164 --> 41:40.874
[Serge] Serge Kylo.
[Marco] Welcome aboard.

41:42.876 --> 41:46.796
I don't like
the word "tribute."

41:46.796 --> 41:49.883
Exchanging crew promotes unity
throughout the Free Navy.

41:49.883 --> 41:52.177
All factions are one.

41:52.177 --> 41:54.554
He's not crew.
He's family.

41:55.680 --> 41:58.558
Let me introduce you to mine.

41:58.558 --> 42:00.477
Filip.

42:03.563 --> 42:04.773
My son.

42:06.441 --> 42:07.984
This is Camina Drummer...

42:09.069 --> 42:11.363
...a patriot

42:11.363 --> 42:14.658
and, uh, a good friend

42:14.658 --> 42:17.327
of your mother.

42:17.327 --> 42:19.162
They were together
on the Behemoth...

42:19.162 --> 42:22.249
before Naomi left her
to join her Inners.

42:22.249 --> 42:25.502
And by doing so,
saved every soul in the system.

42:25.502 --> 42:28.004
I'd like to hear that story.

42:28.004 --> 42:30.257
Another time, perhaps.

42:32.342 --> 42:34.135
Make sure you tell Naomi
what a fine young man

42:34.135 --> 42:36.596
her son has become.

42:36.596 --> 42:38.265
I will.

42:40.517 --> 42:42.978
Is there anything you'd like me
to tell your mother?

42:42.978 --> 42:44.896
There's no need.
I can tell...

42:46.606 --> 42:48.525
No.
Thank you.

42:48.525 --> 42:50.652
[Marco] Good to see you,

42:50.652 --> 42:53.905
as always, Drummer.

42:53.905 --> 43:00.453
♪ ♪

43:17.762 --> 43:20.765
[engines whooshing]

43:31.860 --> 43:38.867
♪ ♪

43:48.168 --> 43:50.295
Tell me about the Behemoth.

43:56.343 --> 43:57.969
[Naomi] It's hard to know
where to start

43:57.969 --> 43:59.346
and even harder to explain

43:59.346 --> 44:00.889
how it ended.

44:03.975 --> 44:05.393
[Filip] Tell me.

44:05.393 --> 44:08.438
How did you open
all the gates?

44:08.438 --> 44:10.065
[Naomi] It wasn't me alone.

44:10.065 --> 44:12.901
It took every one of us
working together.

44:12.901 --> 44:14.110
We all played a part...

44:16.863 --> 44:19.866
[ominous music]

44:19.866 --> 44:26.873
♪ ♪

44:43.515 --> 44:45.100
Did we win?

44:48.895 --> 44:51.022
This round.

44:51.022 --> 44:54.651
We got weapons, food,
transportation.

45:03.910 --> 45:05.286
Thank you.

45:09.833 --> 45:11.709
My clothes?

45:11.709 --> 45:14.295
They had blood
and puke on them.

45:14.295 --> 45:16.131
I found you some new ones here.

45:16.131 --> 45:17.632
They're a little big,
but they'll do.

45:18.883 --> 45:20.260
You okay?

45:22.595 --> 45:24.431
You keep asking me that.

45:25.807 --> 45:27.475
I keep wondering it.

45:29.894 --> 45:32.856
Yeah, I am, actually.

45:33.773 --> 45:35.275
You moved fast.

45:36.609 --> 45:38.987
That's what the mods do.

45:38.987 --> 45:40.655
Is it always like this?

45:41.990 --> 45:43.950
Yeah, pretty much.

45:43.950 --> 45:45.743
Useful in the moment.

45:45.743 --> 45:47.704
It's the moments after
that suck.

45:48.455 --> 45:50.790
That's a shitty design.

45:50.790 --> 45:52.208
I wasn't thinking
about the consequences

45:52.208 --> 45:54.461
when I got them.

45:54.461 --> 45:56.212
Just revenge.

45:56.212 --> 45:58.423
[groans]

45:58.423 --> 45:59.841
Let me see.

46:03.636 --> 46:05.180
All right.

46:26.826 --> 46:28.328
Try not to worry.

46:29.913 --> 46:32.499
I'm not gonna let
anything hurt you.

46:35.585 --> 46:36.961
Thanks.

46:38.588 --> 46:41.007
I heard you talking
in your sleep.

46:41.007 --> 46:44.177
You said something about
monsters and being afraid.

46:47.222 --> 46:50.308
It was a thing from prison.
It...

46:50.308 --> 46:52.560
Creative writing class.
It was stupid.

46:52.560 --> 46:54.437
[laughing] Okay.

46:55.980 --> 46:58.775
I wrote this little...

46:58.775 --> 47:00.527
I don't know...

47:00.527 --> 47:02.362
poem.

47:02.362 --> 47:06.074
Kind of took it on
as a prayer.

47:07.200 --> 47:08.493
How'd it go?

47:10.370 --> 47:12.997
I have killed...

47:12.997 --> 47:14.749
but I'm not a killer,

47:14.749 --> 47:17.961
because a killer is a monster

47:17.961 --> 47:20.964
and monsters aren't afraid.

47:28.930 --> 47:30.848
[sighs]

47:32.934 --> 47:35.019
I'm afraid all the time...

47:36.396 --> 47:39.023
...of the things that I did,

47:39.023 --> 47:42.443
how right it felt
when I was doing them,

47:42.443 --> 47:43.987
how certain I was.

47:43.987 --> 47:46.739
[soft dramatic music]

47:46.739 --> 47:49.617
[breathes deeply]

47:52.787 --> 47:55.373
Why did we come here?

47:55.373 --> 47:56.958
He could've killed you.

47:56.958 --> 47:58.293
Yeah.

47:58.293 --> 48:00.128
But you would've died
on the road.

48:01.421 --> 48:02.964
We needed better supplies
and rest,

48:02.964 --> 48:05.091
and this is where
all those things were.

48:05.091 --> 48:07.552
Does it bother you?

48:07.552 --> 48:09.345
No.

48:09.345 --> 48:11.097
It was worth the risk.

48:11.097 --> 48:13.224
That's not what I mean.

48:13.224 --> 48:17.061
Yeah, the guy was a creep,
but if he hadn't been...

48:17.061 --> 48:18.730
would we have done
something different?

48:19.981 --> 48:21.482
We needed supplies.

48:23.151 --> 48:26.404
We went out of our way
to murder someone

48:26.404 --> 48:28.948
and take his stuff
just 'cause we needed it.

48:30.283 --> 48:33.077
That's not the kind of thing
good people do.

48:33.077 --> 48:36.414
Not even bad people
trying to live like good ones.

48:36.414 --> 48:41.044
♪ ♪

48:41.044 --> 48:43.254
Yeah.

48:43.254 --> 48:45.882
Holden never would've
approved a move like that.

48:45.882 --> 48:50.094
♪ ♪

48:50.094 --> 48:52.096
I need to get back to my crew.

48:52.096 --> 48:59.103
♪ ♪
